'''Isak Malcolm Kwaku Hien''' (born 13 January 1999) is a Swedish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] or [[right-back]] for {{Italian football updater|Atalanta}} club [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]] and the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]].

==Club career==

=== Early career ===
Born in [[Stockholm]], Hien played youth football for [[AIK Fotboll|AIK]], where he played alongside future professional players [[Alexander Isak]] and [[Leopold Wahlstedt]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Hiens pojkdröm - i landslaget med AIK-kompisarna: "Extremt kul" |url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/sverige/hiens-pojkdrom-i-landslaget-med-aik-kompisarna-extremt-kul/ |access-date=22 September 2022 |website=fotbollskanalen |language=sv}}</ref> In 2016, he signed with [[Vasalunds IF]] with which he made his senior debut in [[Division 1 Norra]] in 2017.<ref name=":0" /> Up until the age of 21, he operated mainly as a [[striker (association football)|striker]], but was convinced to switch to [[centre-back]], and flourished in that new position.<ref name=":0" />

=== Djurgårdens IF ===
In 2021, he signed with [[Djurgårdens IF Fotboll|Djurgårdens IF]] before going back to Vasalund on loan during the [[2021 Superettan]] season.<ref name=":0" /> During the [[2022 Djurgårdens IF season|2022 season]], Hien played in 17 games and scored two goals in Allsvenskan before he was signed by [[Serie A]] side [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]].<ref name=":0" />

=== Hellas Verona ===
On 27 August 2022, Hien joined Italian club [[Hellas Verona FC|Hellas Verona]] on a permanent deal, signing a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Hellas Verona|url=https://www.hellasverona.it/it/news/per-la-difesa-gialloblu-ce-isak-hien|title=Per la difesa gialloblù c'è Isak Hien!|date=27 August 2022|access-date=29 August 2022|language=it|archive-date=20 September 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220920163415/https://www.hellasverona.it/it/news/per-la-difesa-gialloblu-ce-isak-hien|url-status=dead}}</ref>

=== Atalanta ===
On 2 January 2024, Hien joined [[Serie A]] side Atalanta, signing a contract until June 2028.<ref>{{cite web |date=2 January 2024 |title=New Year, New Signing! Isak Hien is a Nerazzurro! |url=https://www.atalanta.it/en/news/new-year-new-signing-isak-hien-is-a-nerazzurro/ |access-date=2 January 2024 |publisher=Atalanta BC |language=en}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web |last=Dolci |first=Stefano |date=2 January 2024 |title=Ufficiale, Isak Hien è dell'Atalanta: cifre, dettagli, durata contratto, quanto guadagnerà, quanto incassa il Verona |url=https://www.eurosport.it/calcio/calciomercato/2023-2024/ufficiale-isak-hien-e-dellatalanta-cifre-dettagli-durata-contratto-quanto-guadagnera-quanto-incassa-_sto9941590/story.shtml |access-date=2 January 2024 |website=Eurosport.it |language=it-IT}}</ref> The transfer commanded a reported fee of €9 million.<ref name=":1" />

== International career ==
On 14 September 2022, Hien was selected for the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]] for the first time ahead of their [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League B]] games against [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]] and [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Sport |first=SVT |date=14 September 2022 |title=Fotboll: Tre frågor om Nations League-uttagningen: "Hien ett väldigt spännande namn" |language=sv |work=SVT Sport |url=https://www.svt.se/sport/fotboll/tre-fragor-om-nations-league-uttagningen-hien-ett-valdigt-spannande-namn |access-date=22 September 2022}}</ref> On 24 September 2022, he made his full international debut in a 4–1 loss against Serbia in the [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League B]], playing the full 90 minutes at [[centre-back]] alongside [[List of Sweden men's national football team captains|national team captain]] [[Victor Lindelöf]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Beröm av "VNL" - men Hien splittrad efter debuten |url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/sverige/berom-av-vnl-men-hien-splittrad-efter-debuten/ |access-date=26 September 2022 |website=fotbollskanalen |language=sv}}</ref>

On 12 May 2026, Hien was named in the Sweden squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-12 |title=Mystiskt inlägg efter petningen |url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/landslaget/har-ar-sveriges-trupp-till-fotbolls-vm-2026/ |access-date=2026-05-15 |website=www.expressen.se |language=sv}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Hien was born in [[Sweden]] to a Swedish mother and a [[Ghana]]ian father of [[Burkina Faso|Burkinabé]] descent.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Badia |first1=Tommaso |title=Hien: "Quest'anno ci sarà da divertirsi!" |url=https://www.calciohellas.it/2022/09/14/hien-questanno-ci-sara-da-divertirsi/ |website=Calcio Hellas |access-date=23 January 2023 |language=Italian |date=14 September 2022}}</ref> His brother [[Leon Hien]] is also a professional footballer.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Leon Hien: "Min chans att göra mig ett namn i Sverige" |url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/allsvenskan/leon-hien-min-chans-att-gora-mig-ett-namn-i-sverige/ |access-date=14 February 2025 |website=fotbollskanalen |language=sv}}</ref>

